description.plain:
“Glow” was performed for the first time on YouTube on June 25th, 2020 to celebrate United Nations World Oceans Day.

Later, during an Instagram live (October 25th, 2020) Alice played an acoustic version of the song, with the first guitar she’s ever bought.

The track expresses feelings of confusion, solitude, sadness, anger, and nostalgia, all as the aftermath of a breakup the artist needs to free her mind from.

annotatable.title: Dirty Mouth

annotations: Your sweat tastes salty, your brakes are faulty

This lyric likens their understanding of consent to that of a car with faulty breaks. When you press the breaks a car stops moving but when the breaks are faulty it keeps going. I interpreted this as Alice’s assaulter continuing to touch her without her consent after she said no or “pressed the breaks” meaning their breaks are faulty. This line begins Alice’s recounting of the assault a few lines later she sings “Saying no saying no saying no” which, to me, solidified that this song was about SA.

My body fell asleep when they took it away from me
 But I got it back, now I do what I like with it
 Do what I like with it, do what I like with it,

This verse encompasses the resilient nature of this song. I interpreted it as Alice reclaiming her body after expecting sexual assault. Many survivors of assault experience a disassociation from their bodies following the event explaining the “My body fell asleep when they took it away from me” line. However, this song is about rebounding from that hence “But I got it back now I do what I like with it”. I saw this as Alice reclaiming her body following her assault and freeing herself from the experience. This was a really transformative lyric for and it’s beautifully written.

annotations:
Only when I can’t breathe
 Only when I wanna believe
 Only when it’s late at night
 Only when I don’t feel right
 Only when I touch my body
 Only when I’m feeling naughty
 Only when you’re far away, far away, far away

In an epic reversal that contradicts our expectations, the chorus is a brutally honest admission of undying yearning that makes us know that although she’s learned a lot from the dissolution of her past relationship, she’s not quite done feeling the intense pull in a slew of situations. She longs to be with him when she’s:

inconsolable,
hopeful that he’ll realize what they had was too special to end,
when it’s dark out,
when she’s not feeling herself,
when she’s feeling herself,
so on and so on…

Sometimes it feels like I could give it all up to be held by you
 But that’s not all the time, no, not all the time

She admits her temptation to give almost anything to be back together, but suggests these feelings pass…

but do they?

I’ll spread your love so thickly so I can reminisce some more
 
 Even if we’re done for
 Even if it’s really sore
 I’ll take it all, take it all, take it all
The most direct indications of the song so far that she plans to keep the love a little longer, savor it, even if she’s holding the flame alone
Don’t shut them all too quickly, there might not always be more
Finding love isn’t a guarantee. She asks is closing the door to their love is worth the gamble of potentially never finding love again.

You didn’t teach me, I taught myself through you
 You didn’t heal me, but I healed from the things that you do

Alice suggests that SHE grew as a person after the dissolution of the relationship that she sings in this song. She doesn’t credit her ex for the growth she’s experienced, she claims that for herself.

description.plain:
This song is about reminiscing on a past love, and longing for that feeling of head-over-heels love that consumes one’s entire life. Alice describes how just the look of someone can send you into a hypnotic state, mind racing with thoughts of love and a future with them.

She describes daydreaming about the passion, infatuation, and pure state of bliss that come with a burning love for someone.

She seems to be remembering a childhood love that didn’t work out, and is pondering on her feelings and how it might’ve panned out if things had worked out.

annotations:
It feels like, swimming, swimming with my eyes closed
 Nose to nose, you just, you just fucking know
Alice likens the feeling of gazing into someone’s eyes with absently floating in a pool. It’s a feeling of serenity, and just “being” in the moment.

I spy with my little eye
 Your wide eyes that take me time traveling
Just a look into someone’s eyes is enough to send someone “time traveling” to memories of the past, getting lost in the “maze” of feelings and nostalgia.

I fill myself up with your gaze
 Oh, what a maze you’ve put me in
When you’re fond of someone, just the look of their eyes can send you into a hypnotic state, getting lost in the depth of the other person’s eyes, while your mind races thinking about love.

Suspended in nostalgia
 I find your name hanging in my memories
Nostalgia is a feeling of “a sentimental longing or wistful affection for the past”. Here, it is being applied to a person that Alice is remembering, having their name constantly fill her memories.
